### Description

Standalone migration's `prune-ng-modules` doesn't update imports properly when the pruned NgModule is referenced by a standalone component.

The following code:
```ts
@Component({
  standalone: true,
  template: `<app-child/>`,
  imports: [ChildModule]
})
class App {
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-child',
  standalone: true,
  template: `...`,
})
class Child {
}

@NgModule({
  imports: [Child],
  exports: [Child]
})
class ChildModule {}
```

produces:

```ts
@Component({
  standalone: true,
  template: `<app-child/>`,
  imports: []
})
class App {
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-child',
  standalone: true,
  template: `...`,
})
class Child {
}
```

and breaks the app, while it should produce:


```ts
@Component({
  standalone: true,
  template: `<app-child/>`,
  imports: [Child]
})
class App {
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-child',
  standalone: true,
  template: `...`,
})
class Child {
}
```


